	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" ><blockquote><font face="verdana,arial,helvetica" size="1" >quote:</font><hr><i>Originally posted by Maniacles </i><br />
<b>The real question at this point is, how, exactly, does the new information that being at the top of the hatelist doesn't necessarily generate aggro, due to modifiers, make you want to see taunt changed.  Should it change to maxhate+4?  Should it change to maxhate+maxcurrent modifier? how about maxhate+taunt/n, where n is a number/determined by verant, between 5 and 50?<br />
<br />
If you want taunt changed intelligently, this would be the place to argue.  The taunt mashers would love it, as each use of taunt would add more than just 1 taunt when personally aggroed.</b><hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
What about level aggro and its step sister, sit aggro.  Should a single successful taunt overcome both of those? Could make for some interesting aggro strategies if it does.<br />
<br />
I think while these tests are interesting, they are red herrings.  I believe the real problem is the success rate of taunt, not how it behaves when you are not pressing auto attack.</font></p>
	
