<b>Each time an NPC attacks, and only then, it will decide who to unleash that attack on.  This is what we call aggro.  Aggro will not change between attack rounds, which spell casting also counts as.  At the begginning of each attack round, the NPC analyzes each PC that is on it's hate list.  It adds the hate, and the hate bonus for each PC, and whichever PC has the highest total is the PC that "has aggro" and receives this round of punishment.</b><hr></blockquote> <br />
<br />
Actually, that's not completely true.  Actions are taken based on the hate list between swings.  These include summoning and running after people.  It's quite possible to land a slow, get summoned, and never get hit if the tank wacks taunt as soon as they see the summon message (and taunt successfully).  It's also possible to land a slow, sit, have the mob run toward you, stand, have it move back, all without ever swinging once.</font></p>
	
