	<p><font face="verdana, arial, helvetica" size="2" >Hola-<br />
<br />
I tend to agree w/ Tugurok- I'm a "constant taunter" (hey, tanking can get boring, and it's an extra button to wait for ungreying, so I can click it again! <img src="images/smilies/smile.gif" border="0" alt=""> ) but I typically get unshakeable aggro even in relatively high dps groups despite taunting constantly.  I will start watching for indications of this tho...<br />
<br />
Pseudocode from link:<br />
if(YOUR_AGRO_SLOT==1 && AGRO_SLOT(1) != LOWHP_AGRO)<br />
&#123;Set YOUR_AGRO_TOTAL to AGRO_SLOT(2)+1;<br />
}<br />
else (Set YOUR_AGRO_TOTAL to AGRO_SLOT(1)+1) ;<br />
<br />
I don't see any real reason they'd code it this way; it'd probably be much more efficient to use the aggro list as an index instead of some "aggro slot" construct, for example.  Anything done that frequently in-game is gonna be highly optimized, and that first "set" is entirely redundant (would be a no-op if anything...).<br />
<br />
IANAPP tho.<br />
RdT.</font></p>
	
